      <name>Arashiyama Sakura </name>
      <description><![CDATA[<strong>Arashiyama Sakura </strong><br/>Kyoto / Arashiyama Furonohashicho<br/>Address: 20-6, Arashiyama Furonohashicho, Nishikyo-ku, Kyoto-shi, Kyoto<br/>Nearest: 6-minute walk from Matsuo-taisha Station on the Hankyu Arashiyama Line<br/>Cuisine: Japanese, Kaiseki, Washoku<br/>Reservation: Request booking<br/>Dinner range: $$$ JPY 10k-20k<br/>Lunch range: $$ JPY 5k-10k<br/>Child policy: Children can visit the restaurant as long as they are of junior high school age or older and can eat the same courses as adults.<br/>Summary: Customers can enjoy a memorable food experience with seasonal Kyoto cuisine.<br/>Known for: Hidden spot, Seasonal cooking, Private room option<br/>Signature cues: Kaiseki, Kyoto cuisine, Omakase<br/><a href="https://pocket-concierge.jp/en/restaurants/244312/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Pocket Concierge</a><br/>Source venue coordinates from Pocket Concierge.]]></description>
      <Point>
        <coordinates>135.687294,35.005997,0</coordinates>
